01_globalmem

Description:
The demo would create a device file, you can use  "open, write, read, ioctl" to 
control the device.  

The advantage is to interact with a device resources in kernel space.


Some Instructions:

> make 
> insmod globalmem.ko

> echo "hello world" > /dev/globalmem
> cat /dev/globalmem

> ./write
> ./read

> rmmod globalmem

> make clean
